JENKINS INSTALLATION GUIDE  (Youtube Channel Name : Easytech_9S) {DAY-1}

PRE-REQUISITE

EC2 (AMAZON LINUX t2.medium)
Enable Port Number (Custom TCP =  8080)

Commands :

sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo

sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key

sudo yum upgrade

sudo dnf install java-17-amazon-corretto-devel
 
sudo yum install jenkins

sudo systemctl enable jenkins

sudo systemctl start jenkins

sudo systemctl status jenkins

JENKINS INTEGRATION WITH GITHUB {DAY-2}
Step-1  Install Git in jenkins Sever (Command --> sudo yum install git -y)
Step-2  Jenkins Dashboard --> FreeStyle Project --> Source Code Management --> O Git --> Repository URL & Credentials (Give This Info Here) -->Branches to build
(Specify Github repo Branch) --> Apply & Save --> Build now 

JENKINS INTEGRATION WITH MAVEN {DAY-3}
Step-1 Jenkins Dashboard --> Manage Jenkins --> Pulgins --> Availabale Pulgins --> Maven Integration plugin (Search & Install) .
Step-2 Jenkins Dashboard --> Manage Jenkins --> Tools --> Maven installations (Scroll Down) --> Name & Version (Add) --> Apply & Save 
Step-3 Jenkins Dashboard --> FreeStyle Project --> Build Steps --> Build Steps --> Invoke top-level Maven targets --> Maven Version & Goals (Specify here) --> Build now 
 

